            About
            I’m an entomologist specializing in the evolution of
            twisted-wing insect parasites (Strepsiptera) for my PhD in
            Comparative Biology at the American Museum of Natural
            History. My work involves the genomics, host associations,
            and speciation of this enigmatic order.
            This site essentially exists for me to practice my
            programming—in R, CSS, HTML, etc. and to keep a log of what
            I’ve been working on. I don’t really know what I’m doing,
            but I’m having a good time. Occasionally the last part is a
            lie because learning how to code solo is frustrating
            sometimes.
